<TITLE> Murder over love affair </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 22 (bdnews24.com) -- A young garment worker was murdered on Wednesday allegedly for having a love affair with the daughter of his rich landlord. Relatives of victim Russell, 19, alleged that four paternal uncles of Barsha, 15, with whom he had an affair for 2 and half years, beat him to death on Wednesday. Russell's uncle Shah Alam told bdnews24 that the four -- Kamal, Kalam, Aslam and Tulu -- forcibly took Russell, his brother Rubel and sister in-law to their house at around 3am on Wednesday as Barsha came to Rubel's house. He said they beat the three and later detained only Russell letting the others free. Russel's father Md Selim told bdnews24.com that at 11pm Tulu called his brother-in-law Shah Alam to collect the body of Russel from Mitford hospital. At the hospital they found Russel lying dead. "His body bore numerous injury marks," he said. Officer in-charge of Mohammadpur police station Bhuiyan Mahbub Hasan told bdnews24.com that they recovered the body from the hospital after hearing the incident and arranged for post mortem. He said police has already launched drive to arrest the alleged murderers. Russell's relatives said the murderers have gone into hiding. The victim was a worker at a garment factory near the Mohammadpur bus stand supermarket. He lived with his parents in a nearby tin-shed house. Barsha is the daughter of one Barkat, supposedly a rich man in the Mohammadpur area. bdn
